sql:
SELECT model_id, AVG(training_time) AS average_training_time
FROM training_metrics
GROUP BY model_id;

SELECT average_return
FROM training_metrics
ORDER BY iteration;

external_knowledge:
- A "marathon" refers to a training run in this context; 
- A "champion" refers to the model being trained, identified by a unique model name; 
- "taken more than a century to prepare" refers to the average training time exceeding 100 seconds; 
- "impressive performance variations" refers to the maximum explained variance of the model's predictions.

- The term "best run" refers to the training run that yields the highest average return for a given model; 
- Average return is a measure of the model's performance during training;
- Average training time refers to the average time taken by a model to complete its training iterations;
- The training runs are ordered by their start times to provide a chronological view of the models' performance.
